# Content & Lessons Guide

> This guide applies to **every CEFR level** (A1, A2, B1, B2). The same
> templates, types, exercise components, i18n, TTS pipeline and quality
> checklist are shared across all levels. Each level has its own content
> folder; the rest of the platform is level-agnostic.

## Folder Layout (Multi-Level)

```
src/content/
вФЬвФАвФА shared/                вЖР types, EXERCISE_TEMPLATES, TEST_TEMPLATES (USED BY ALL LEVELS)
вФЬвФАвФА a1/
вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА lessons/lesson-XX/ вЖР A1 lesson folders (folder name == lesson id)
вФВ   вФЬвФАвФА tests/test-вА¶/
вФВ   вФФвФАвФА index.ts           вЖР A1 registry: loaders, navItems, metadata
вФЬвФАвФА a2/                    вЖР same shape
вФЬвФАвФА b1/, b2/               вЖР same shape (skeletons)
вФЬвФАвФА registry.ts            вЖР global cross-level registry (loaders, lookups)
вФФвФАвФА index.ts               вЖР public barrel: types + helpers + registry
```

When adding a new exercise type, template, or rule, put it in `shared/` so it
is available for every level вАФ never duplicate per level.

## Lesson Folder Structure

Each lesson lives in `src/content/<level>/lessons/<lesson-id>/` with 5 files:

- `metadata.ts` вАФ id, number, title, description, grammarTopics[], vocabulary[]
- `content.ts` вАФ introduction text, dialogues, sections
- `exercises.ts` вАФ ALL lesson elements in PDF order (exercises + –Э–Ю–Т–Ш –Ф–£–Ь–Ш + –У–†–Р–Ь–Р–Ґ–Ш–Ъ–Р + –Ф–Ш–Р–Ы–Ю–Ч–Ш)
- `workbook.ts` вАФ workbook-only exercises
- `index.ts` вАФ re-exports everything as `lessonData`

After creating the files, register the lesson **in the level's index file**
(e.g. `src/content/a2/index.ts`) by adding entries to:

- `<LEVEL>_LESSON_LOADERS` вАФ `'a2-lesson-01': () => import('./lessons/a2-lesson-01')`
- `<LEVEL>_LESSONS_METADATA` вАФ id, number, title, hasTest, testId
- `<LEVEL>_NAV_ITEMS` вАФ sidebar entry
- `<LEVEL>_LESSON_EXERCISE_COUNTS` вАФ total interactive exercises (for sidebar %)

The cross-level `src/content/registry.ts` automatically picks the new entries
up; routes (`/lessons/[lessonId]`, `/tests/[testId]`) work without changes.

## ID Naming Conventions

A1 lesson IDs are kept un-prefixed (`lesson-XX`) for backward compatibility
with existing user progress in the database. **A2 / B1 / B2 lesson IDs are
level-prefixed** (`a2-lesson-XX`, `b1-lesson-XX`, вА¶) so they never collide
with A1.

| Element | A1 format | A2+ format |
|---|---|---|
| Lesson | `lesson-XX` (e.g. `lesson-02`) | `a2-lesson-XX`, `b1-lesson-XX`, вА¶ |
| Exercise | `lXX-ex-NN` (e.g. `l02-ex-01`) | `a2-lXX-ex-NN`, `b1-lXX-ex-NN`, вА¶ |
| Workbook | `lXX-wb-NN` | `a2-lXX-wb-NN`, вА¶ |
| –Э–Њ–≤–Є –і—Г–Љ–Є | `lXX-novi-dumi-NN` | `a2-lXX-novi-dumi-NN`, вА¶ |
| –У—А–∞–Љ–∞—В–Є–Ї–∞ | `lXX-gramatika-NN` | `a2-lXX-gramatika-NN`, вА¶ |
| –Ф–Є–∞–ї–Њ–Ј–Є | `lXX-dialozi-NN` | `a2-lXX-dialozi-NN`, вА¶ |
| Test | `test-a1-N` (e.g. `test-a1-3`) | `test-a2-N`, `test-b1-N`, вА¶ |

## Asset Paths

Assets go in `/public/assets/<lesson-id>/` with descriptive subfolders. The
folder name **matches the lesson ID** (so A1 uses `/public/assets/lesson-02/`
and A2 uses `/public/assets/a2-lesson-01/`):

- `audio/tts/` вАФ generated TTS MP3 files (see `tts-audio` rule)
- `audio/` вАФ other audio files
- `exercise-NN-name/` вАФ images for a specific exercise
- `novi-dumi-N-name/` вАФ vocabulary card images
- `gramatika-N/` вАФ grammar section images

Source files (PDFs, audio, images) are on the developer's machine at:
`C:\Users\Work Account\Desktop\CURSOR\GITHUB A1\a1-files\lessons\lesson-X\` (A1)
or the equivalent A2/B1/B2 source folders.

## exercises.ts вАФ Key Rules

- ALL lesson elements go here: exercises AND vocabulary sections AND grammar sections AND dialogues
- The `order` field must match the exact sequence in the PDF
- Informational sections (–Э–Ю–Т–Ш –Ф–£–Ь–Ш, –У–†–Р–Ь–Р–Ґ–Ш–Ъ–Р, –Ф–Ш–Р–Ы–Ю–Ч–Ш) have no `points` field
- Actual exercises have a `points` field
- **`points` = number of blanks/questions, NOT number of sentences.** For `table_fill`, points = number of rows.
- **Do NOT duplicate examples as interactive items.** If `isExample: true`, it must not count toward points.
- Instructions must match the **digital-format standards** вАФ see `content-quality-checklist.mdc` ¬ІA3 for the standardized instruction table per exercise type. Do NOT copy verbatim from the textbook; do NOT improvise new instructions for standard exercise types.
- When a lesson has **multiple sections of the same type**, always number them: –Э–Ю–Т–Ш –Ф–£–Ь–Ш 1, –Э–Ю–Т–Ш –Ф–£–Ь–Ш 2... / –У–†–Р–Ь–Р–Ґ–Ш–Ъ–Р 1, 2... / –Ф–Ш–Р–Ы–Ю–Ч–Ш 1, 2...
- All –Э–Ю–Т–Ш –Ф–£–Ь–Ш sections in **—Г—А–Њ—Ж–Є 0вАУ1 and –Р–Ј–±—Г–Ї–∞** must use instruction: `'–Э–∞—В–Є—Б–љ–µ—В–µ –Ј–∞ –њ—А–Њ–Є–Ј–љ–Њ—И–µ–љ–Є–µ.'`
- –Э–Ю–Т–Ш –Ф–£–Ь–Ш sections in **—Г—А–Њ—Ж–Є 2+** use **no instruction** (rely on card-level рЯФК icons only).
- Dialogues: verify **every line** is complete and matches the textbook exactly.
- **Currency rule:** –ї–µ–≤–∞ вЖТ –µ–≤—А–Њ, —Б—В–Њ—В–Є–љ–Ї–Є вЖТ –µ–≤—А–Њ—Ж–µ–љ—В–∞. All monetary exercises must use `dropdown` input (not free text).
- Short fill-in-blank exercises (e.g., –і–≤–∞/–і–≤–µ, –Ї–∞–Ї—К–≤/–Ї–∞–Ї–≤–∞) вЖТ use `layout: 'two-column'`.
- `content.ts` dialogues **must match** `exercises.ts` dialogues exactly (same lines, same prices, same currency).
- Empty `imageUrl: ''` is safe вАФ components (`IllustratedCards`, `GrammarWithExamples`) skip rendering when empty.
- **`grammar_examples` label field:** Use `label` for visual-only annotations (e.g. `'–Ъ–∞–Ї—К–≤ вАФ –Љ—К–ґ–Ї–Є —А–Њ–і'`). Shown as a green badge below the card content. **NOT read by TTS** вАФ keeps audio clean while displaying grammatical info.
- **Content guideline for TTS:** In dialogue lines with numbers/sums, prefer a **period** over a dash (e.g. `'–†–µ—Б—В–Њ—В–Њ. –І–µ—В–Є—А–Є –µ–≤—А–Њ.'` not `'–†–µ—Б—В–Њ—В–Њ вАФ —З–µ—В–Є—А–Є –µ–≤—А–Њ.'`). The dash confuses TTS pronunciation and pacing.
- **`grammar_table` alignment rule:** `columns.length` MUST equal `cells.length` for every row. The `pronoun` field renders in the first column automatically (with an empty header). Do NOT include the pronoun column label in `columns` вАФ it causes header misalignment.
- **`grammar_table` bolding вАФ choose the right tool:** `boldColumns: [n]` bolds the ENTIRE column (header + cells). Inline `**word**` inside a cell bolds ONLY that word/ending (e.g. вАЮ–њ–∞–Ј–∞—А**—К—В**", вАЮ–і–≤–µ —П–±—К–ї–Ї**–Є**"). Use inline `**` when you want to highlight noun endings / articles per word вАФ using `boldColumns` would make the table heavy and unreadable. Markdown is stripped before TTS.
- **Instruction text must match the actual exercise type.** If the exercise uses dropdowns, the instruction should say "–Ш–Ј–±–µ—А–µ—В–µ" (Select), not "–Э–∞–њ–Є—И–µ—В–µ" (Write). Match the verb to the interaction: Select вЖТ dropdown, Write вЖТ text input, Arrange вЖТ drag-and-drop.

## Grammar Info Box (`grammar_highlight`)

For visually prominent grammar notes that need to stand out from the exercise body (e.g. the —Б/—Б—К—Б rule in l2 ex 12, or the million/milliard rule in l5 ex 31), add a `grammarHighlight` object to the exercise:

```ts
grammarHighlight: {
  textKey: 'exercise.sSusWith',  // key in ui.ts (pre-translated on 7 languages)
  // OR inline text if translation will be auto:
  // text: '–Ъ–Њ–≥–∞—В–Њ –і—Г–Љ–∞ —Б–ї–µ–і вАЮ—Б" ...',
}
```

The component renders it as a green info box with an вАЮвДє" icon above the exercise body. Add the translation key to `src/i18n/ui.ts` on all 7 languages.

