## Content Quality Standards (from feedback on lessons 0вАУ6)

See `content-quality-checklist` rule for the FULL checklist. Key rules to remember here:

- **Instructions adapted for digital:** Do NOT copy textbook instructions verbatim. The textbook is paper вАФ our platform is interactive. Every instruction must describe what the user does IN THE APP (dropdown вЖТ вАЮ–Ш–Ј–±–µ—А–µ—В–µ", drag вЖТ вАЮ–Я–ї—К–Ј–љ–µ—В–µ", etc.). Remove paper references: вАЮ–њ–Њ –і–≤–Њ–є–Ї–Є", вАЮ–љ–∞ —Е–∞—А—В–Є—П", вАЮ–≤ —В–µ—В—А–∞–і–Ї–∞—В–∞".
- **No component shuffle:** `word_order.words[]`, `syllable_blocks.syllables[]`, `dialogue_builder.sentences[]` вАФ the component does NOT shuffle. Elements show EXACTLY in array order. Arrange them maximally scrambled when defining the content.
- **Mix true/false:** In `true_false` and checklist exercises, interleave correct and incorrect items (never group all correct first).
- **Numbers as words for TTS:** In `listeningText` and text paragraphs meant for audio, write numbers as words (76 вЖТ вАЮ—Б–µ–і–µ–Љ–і–µ—Б–µ—В –Є —И–µ—Б—В") so TTS pronounces them correctly.
- **First word capitalized:** Every sentence in options, true_false items, and table cells must start with a capital letter.
- **No definite article with possessives:** вАЮ–±–∞–±–∞" not вАЮ–±–∞–±–∞—В–∞" when preceded by a possessive pronoun (–Љ–Њ—П—В–∞ –±–∞–±–∞).
- **Review section:** Title is вАЮ–Я—А–µ–≥–Њ–≤–Њ—А", subtitle is вАЮ–£–њ—А–∞–ґ–љ–µ–љ–Є—П –Ј–∞ –Ј–∞—В–≤—К—А–ґ–і–∞–≤–∞–љ–µ –љ–∞ –љ–∞—Г—З–µ–љ–Њ—В–Њ". Never use вАЮ–Њ—В —А–∞–±–Њ—В–љ–∞—В–∞ —В–µ—В—А–∞–і–Ї–∞".
- **Grammar table subtitle вЖТ subtext:** Explanatory text goes as grey subtext under the exercise title, never as a separate boxed block.
- **textTitle for reading_text:** When a text has a title (e.g. вАЮ–С—К–ї–≥–∞—А–Є—П –µ —Е—Г–±–∞–≤–∞ —Б—В—А–∞–љ–∞"), set `textTitle` to show it bold above the paragraphs.
- **showDictionary for reading_text:** Set `showDictionary: true` on reading exercises with real vocabulary (not on test exercises with `noTranslation`).
- **–Э–Ю–Т–Ш –Ф–£–Ь–Ш before exercises:** Vocabulary sections must come BEFORE exercises that use those words. If a reading text uses new vocabulary, place the text AFTER the –Э–Ю–Т–Ш –Ф–£–Ь–Ш section.
- **Grammar rule before practice:** If an exercise applies a grammar rule (e.g. articles), the rule must be shown BEFORE the exercise.

### Pre-translation (`instructionKey`) rules

Grammar instructions and complex exercise instructions MUST be pre-translated via `instructionKey` in `ui.ts`. Auto-translation (`useTranslate`) is NOT reliable for:
- Linguistic terminology (—А–Њ–і, —З–ї–µ–љ, —Б–њ—А–µ–ґ–µ–љ–Є–µ, –Љ–љ–Њ–ґ–µ—Б—В–≤–µ–љ–Њ —З–Є—Б–ї–Њ...)
- Instructions describing new interaction patterns (drag, swipe, column sorting...)
- Grammar notes with Bulgarian-specific examples

Simple, repetitive instructions (e.g. вАЮ–Я–Њ–њ—К–ї–љ–µ—В–µ –њ—А–∞–Ј–љ–Є—В–µ –Љ–µ—Б—В–∞.") can use auto-translation.

## Automatic UI Behaviors (no action needed in content files)

The following behaviors are built into the exercise components вАФ content authors don't need to do anything extra:

- **Options are shuffled** вАФ `WorkbookFillBlank` shuffles `options[]` on render so the correct answer isn't always first.
- **Letters are shuffled** вАФ `LetterChoice` shuffles the letter pool on render.
- **Reset button** вАФ ALL interactive exercise components show a "Reset" button. If a component is missing one, it is a bug вАФ report/fix it.
- **TTS** вАФ Components prefer pre-generated MP3 via `getTtsAudioPath()`, with browser `speakBulgarian()` as fallback. See `tts-audio` rule for generation details.

## Alternative Correct Answers

When an exercise has **multiple valid answers** for the same question:

**`dropdown_match`** вАФ use `alternateCorrectAnswers`:
```ts
{ id: 'q2', left: '–Ф–Њ–±—К—А', options: [...], correctAnswer: '–і–µ–љ!', alternateCorrectAnswers: ['–≤–µ—З–µ—А!'] }
```

**`dialogue_builder`** вАФ use `alternateOrders` on the section:
```ts
{ id: '–≤.', givenFirstLine: '...', sentences: [...], alternateOrders: [[...], [...]] }
```

**`workbook_fill_blank`** вАФ use `acceptableAnswers`:
```ts
{ text: '...', correctAnswers: ['—В—П –µ —Г–Ї—А–∞–Є–љ–Ї–∞.'], acceptableAnswers: [['—В—П –µ —Г–Ї—А–∞–Є–љ–Ї–∞', '—В—П –µ —Г–Ї—А–∞–Є–љ–Ї–∞.']] }
```

## Creating Exercises вАФ ALWAYS Use Templates

When creating exercises, **always read [src/content/shared/EXERCISE_TEMPLATES.ts](mdc:src/content/shared/EXERCISE_TEMPLATES.ts) first**.
Copy the relevant template and replace only the content вАФ never write exercise structure from scratch.

